  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Klebsiella pneumonia, inhabitant of the digestive tract, is a frequent nosocomial pathogen.
      It is currently the fourth most common cause of pneumonia and fifth most common cause of
      bacteremia in intensive care patients (1-3).

      The aim of the present randomized controlled trial is to assess the efficacy of
      non-absorbable oral antibiotics in the eradication of the KPC carrier state.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
